{"key":"post-7874131","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7874131</id>\n<content>Boiling won't add much water to the grains after a 24 hour soak.  In fact, I always follow up the soak with a boil just so the grains will be hot when I drain them.  This way, they both drain and steam, leaving them dry on the outside.  When the surface of the grains are dry, load jars and pressure cook.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7874679</next>\n<prev>7873853</prev>\n<first>7873176</first>\n<last>7875747</last>\n<when>1200266444</when>\n<utime>01/14/08 01:20 AM</utime>\n</post>"}